you mixed up the purpose of the files. 
The main difference between `settings.gradle` and `lib/build.gradle` lies in their scope and purpose:
- `settings.gradle` defines the global project settings and project structure, applied globally to all modules in the project.
- `lib/build.gradle` contains build script instructions and settings specific to a particular module.

In your case, these files should be like this.

1. `settings.gradle` file:
```groovy
plugins {
    id &#39;org.gradle.toolchains.foojay-resolver-convention&#39; version &#39;0.5.0&#39;
}

rootProject.name = &#39;demo&#39;
include(&#39;lib&#39;)

```

2. `lib/build.gradle` file:
```groovy
plugins {
    id &#39;java-library&#39;
}

repositories {
    mavenCentral()
}

dependencies {
    implementation &#39;com.google.auto.service:auto-service:1.1.1&#39;
}
```

And make sure you are using `gradle` version 7.6.1+

I hope this helps you. Good luck!

