Here is a different guess of what could cause the error:

You mentioned that you use spring batch and spring batch has a Transaction per chunk **already**.

Given the following code:

    @Transaction
    public void foo(Object obj){
        repository.save(obj);
    }

What happens behind the scenes is that the code gets proxied to something like this:

    public void foo(Object obj){
        try {
            repository.save(obj);
        } catch(Exception e){
            markForRollback();
            throw e;
        }
    }

you are catching the exception one level higher:

    public void abc(){
        try {
            foo(obj); //here the first save throws, goes throug the proxied code, gets rethrown and is caught here
        } catch(Exception e){
            log.error(&quot;error!&quot;);
        }
    } 

But this means that the markForRollback() is getting executed! Since you already have a transaction because of spring batch, the whole batch is **likely** getting rolled back (but not sure here! thats why its a guess) at the end of the chunk.

You can try 3 things:

* move the try catch code into the saveMemberItems method
* remove the @Transactional annotation, because then the proxy is not markign the whole transaction for rollback
* You can change the annotation to: @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW), which means a new transaction is getting created and you **only** rollback the first save and nothing more

I would go for the second solution

